<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lame1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lame,</orth> adj. 1) crippled, disabled in the feet: <bibl n="shak. luc 902" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 902</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.291" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 291</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 95</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 3, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 4</bibl>. Used of verses: <cit><quote>the feet were l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.178" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 178</bibl></cit>. <emph>on the l. feet of my rhyme,</emph> Per. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.0." default="NO" valid="yes">IV Prol. 48</bibl>.<lb />2) disabled in any manner, impaired in strength: <cit><quote>made l. by fortune's dearest spite,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 37.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 37, 3</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. son 37.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 37, 3</bibl> <cit><quote>youth is nimble, age is l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 162" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 162</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>when service should in my old limbs lie l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.3.41" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 3, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. of sense,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 63</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>most l. and impotent conclusion,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.162" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 162</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>